Change History

Revision Date Notes
3.0.0 2020-08-01
  • Added NetworkSecurity3 service to indicate support for shield phase 2 features.
  • Added GetNetworkSecuritySettings2 action, which includes the following changes:
    • Renamed isNetworkSecurityEnabled to isParentalControlEnabled
    • Added isThreatDetectionEnabled
    • Added isMaliciousWebsiteDetectionEnabled
  • Added SetNetworkSecuritySettings2 action, which includes the following changes:
    • Renamed isNetworkSecurityEnabled to isParentalControlEnabled
    • Added isThreatDetectionEnabled
    • Added isMaliciousWebsiteDetectionEnabled
  • Added GetThreatSignatureStatus action.
  • Added SyncLogFiles action.
2.0.0 2019-07-17 Added NetworkSecurity2 service to indicate the following action now requires authentication:
  • GetNetworkSecuritySettings
1.0.1 2018-05-08 In order to support local login:
  • Added licenseID to GetSubscriptionStatus.
  • Removed NoLicense from SubscriptionStatus.
1.0.0 2018-02-14 Initial release.

Services

ConfigVersion1

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/ConfigVersion1
The presence of this service indicates that version #1 of the network security configuration is supported by the firmware.

Service Actions

This service does not include any actions.

NetworkSecurity

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/NetworkSecurity
This service provides access to a router's subscription-based network security feature.

Service Actions

  • GetBackupConfigurationInfo
  • GetNetworkSecuritySettings
  • GetSubscriptionStatus
  • RestoreConfiguration
  • SetNetworkSecuritySettings

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/NetworkSecurity2

Actions

GetBackupConfigurationInfo

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetBackupConfigurationInfo
This action gets information about a backup configuration in the cloud.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isBackupAvailable bool no Whether a backup configuration for the router is available in the cloud.
configVersion int yes The version number of the backup configuration. This parameter will be present only if isBackupAvailable is true. The value of this parameter is used to determine whether the backup configuration can be restored, as follows: If configVersion is X, and service ConfigVersionX exists, then the backup configuration can be restored. Otherwise, the version is no longer supported.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetBackupConfigurationInfoResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorCloudUnavailable Failed retrieving the backup configuration information because the cloud service is not available.
ErrorNoWANConnection The WAN connection is down.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorDisallowedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetBackupConfigurationInfo"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "isBackupAvailable": true,
    "configVersion": 123
  }
}

GetNetworkSecuritySettings

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetNetworkSecuritySettings
This action gets the current network security settings on the router.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isNetworkSecurityEnabled bool no Whether network security is enabled on the router.
engineConfigs ConfigurationSettings no The current configuration settings.
supportedCategories SupportedCategory[] no A list of supported categories.
predefinedFilters PredefinedFilter[] no List of pre-defined filters.
maxRuleDescriptionLength int no The maximum length, in bytes, of a rule's description.
maxRuleMACAddresses int no The maximum number of MAC addresses that can be specified by a rule.
maxRuleBlockedURLLength int no The maximum length, in bytes, of a blocked URL specified by a rule.
maxRuleBlockedURLs int no The maximum number of blocked URLs that a rule can specify.
maxRuleAllowedURLLength int no The maximum length, in bytes, of an allowed URL specified by a rule.
maxTotalAllowedURLs int no The maximum number of allowed URLs that can be specified.
maxRules int no The maximum number of rules that can exist simultaneously.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetNetworkSecuritySettingsResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

GetNetworkSecuritySettings2

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetNetworkSecuritySettings2
This action gets the current network security settings on the router.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isParentalControlEnabled bool no Whether parental control is enabled on the router.
isThreatDetectionEnabled bool no Whether threat detection is enabled on the router.
isMaliciousWebsiteDetectionEnabled bool no Whether malicious website detection is enabled on the router.
engineConfigs ConfigurationSettings no The current configuration settings.
supportedCategories SupportedCategory[] no A list of supported categories.
predefinedFilters PredefinedFilter[] no List of pre-defined filters.
maxRuleDescriptionLength int no The maximum length, in bytes, of a rule's description.
maxRuleMACAddresses int no The maximum number of MAC addresses that can be specified by a rule.
maxRuleBlockedURLLength int no The maximum length, in bytes, of a blocked URL specified by a rule.
maxRuleBlockedURLs int no The maximum number of blocked URLs that a rule can specify.
maxRuleAllowedURLLength int no The maximum length, in bytes, of an allowed URL specified by a rule.
maxTotalAllowedURLs int no The maximum number of allowed URLs that can be specified.
maxRules int no The maximum number of rules that can exist simultaneously.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetNetworkSecuritySettings2Result

OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

GetSubscriptionStatus

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetSubscriptionStatus
This action gets the status of the network security subscription on the router.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

This action does not have any input parameters.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
licenseID string yes The vendor license ID of the network security subscription. This parameter exists if and only if the license ID has been set via SetNetworkSecuritySettings.
subscriptionStatus SubscriptionStatus no The current status of the network security subscription.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetSubscriptionStatusResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/GetSubscriptionStatus"

{
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "licenseID": "IHavePaidSoSecureMyWorld",
    "subscriptionStatus": "Active"
  }
}

This action does not have any output parameters.

Error

ErrorInvalidLicenseID The input licenseID cannot be an empty string.
ErrorNoWANConnection The WAN connection is down.

SetNetworkSecuritySettings

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/SetNetworkSecuritySettings
This action sets the network security settings on the router.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isNetworkSecurityEnabled bool no Whether network security should be enabled on the router.
licenseID string yes The vendor license ID of the network security subscription. Activation/Re-activation will be triggered when this value changes. To clear the stored license ID, do not pass this value in.
engineConfigs ConfigurationSettings no The configuration settings object that will be passed to the network security engine.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/SetNetworkSecuritySettingsResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorAllowedURLTooLong One of the allowed URLs of one of the specified rules was longer than the maximum allowed length specified by the maxRuleAllowedURLLengthmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorBlockedURLTooLong One of the blocked URLs of one of the specified rules was longer than the maximum allowed length specified by the maxRuleBlockedURLLengthmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorConfigurationSettingsWriteFailed Error occured when writing the configuration settings to a file.
ErrorDescriptionTooLong The description of one of the specified rules was longer than the maximum allowed length specified by the maxRuleDescriptionLength member of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorInvalidLicenseID The input licenseID cannot be an empty string.
ErrorInvalidMACAddress One of the specified rules contains an invalid MAC address.
ErrorInvalidWANSchedule One of the specified rules contains an invalid internet block schedule.
ErrorMissingInternetBlockSchedule One of the specified device specific rules is missing InternetBlockSchedule.
ErrorMissingMACAddress One of the specified device specific rules is missing a MAC address.
ErrorRulesOverlap A MAC address was specified more than once in the list of rules.
ErrorScheduleExceptionsOverlap A MAC address was specified in both schedule exception lists
ErrorSuperfluousInternetBlockSchedule Internet block schedule is specified in globalProfile.
ErrorSuperfluousMACAddress One or more MAC addresses is specified in globalProfile.
ErrorTooManyAllowedURLs One of the specified rules contains more than the maximum allowed number of allowed URLs specified by the maxRuleAllowedURLsmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorTooManyBlockedURLs One of the specified rules contains more than the maximum allowed number of blocked URLs specified by the maxRuleBlockedURLsmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorTooManyMACAddresses One of the specified rules contains more than the maximum allowed number of MAC addresses specified by the maxRuleMACAddressesmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorTooManyRules The specified list of rules contains more than the maximum allowed number of rules specified by the maxRules member of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

SetNetworkSecuritySettings2

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/SetNetworkSecuritySettings2
This action sets the network security settings on the router.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
isParentalControlEnabled bool no Whether parental control should be enabled on the router.
isThreatDetectionEnabled bool no Whether threat detection is enabled on the router.
isMaliciousWebsiteDetectionEnabled bool no Whether malicious website detection is enabled on the router.
licenseID string yes The vendor license ID of the network security subscription. Activation/Re-activation will be triggered when this value changes. To clear the stored license ID, do not pass this value in.
engineConfigs ConfigurationSettings no The configuration settings object that will be passed to the network security engine.

Output Parameters

This action does not have any output parameters.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/SetNetworkSecuritySettings2Result
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorAllowedURLTooLong One of the allowed URLs of one of the specified rules was longer than the maximum allowed length specified by the maxRuleAllowedURLLengthmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorBlockedURLTooLong One of the blocked URLs of one of the specified rules was longer than the maximum allowed length specified by the maxRuleBlockedURLLengthmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorConfigurationSettingsWriteFailed Error occured when writing the configuration settings to a file.
ErrorDescriptionTooLong The description of one of the specified rules was longer than the maximum allowed length specified by the maxRuleDescriptionLength member of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorInvalidLicenseID The input licenseID cannot be an empty string.
ErrorInvalidMACAddress One of the specified rules contains an invalid MAC address.
ErrorInvalidWANSchedule One of the specified rules contains an invalid internet block schedule.
ErrorMissingInternetBlockSchedule One of the specified device specific rules is missing InternetBlockSchedule.
ErrorMissingMACAddress One of the specified device specific rules is missing a MAC address.
ErrorRulesOverlap A MAC address was specified more than once in the list of rules.
ErrorScheduleExceptionsOverlap A MAC address was specified in both schedule exception lists
ErrorSuperfluousInternetBlockSchedule Internet block schedule is specified in globalProfile.
ErrorSuperfluousMACAddress One or more MAC addresses is specified in globalProfile.
ErrorTooManyAllowedURLs One of the specified rules contains more than the maximum allowed number of allowed URLs specified by the maxRuleAllowedURLsmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorTooManyBlockedURLs One of the specified rules contains more than the maximum allowed number of blocked URLs specified by the maxRuleBlockedURLsmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorTooManyMACAddresses One of the specified rules contains more than the maximum allowed number of MAC addresses specified by the maxRuleMACAddressesmember of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings action.
ErrorTooManyRules The specified list of rules contains more than the maximum allowed number of rules specified by the maxRules member of the GetNetworkSecuritySettings
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Structures

ConfigurationSettings

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/ConfigurationSettings
The configuration settings that will be pushed to the router.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
internetBlockScheduleExceptions InternetBlockScheduleExceptions no Devices specified in the following list is blocked from using the internet. This list has the highest precedence.
profiles NetworkSecurityProfiles no Contains global profile and device-specific profiles.

InternetBlockPeriod

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/InternetBlockPeriod
A period that is represented by a start time and an end time in a 24-hour format. The valid range is from 00:00 to 24:00. Specifying startTime as 00:00 and endTime as 24:00 will block the device for the whole day.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
startTime string no The start time of the time blocking period.
endTime string no The end time of the time blocking period.

InternetBlockSchedule

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/InternetBlockSchedule
A schedule specifying when WAN access should be disabled during a calendar week. If no schedule blocking is desired, send 0-length arrays.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
sunday InternetBlockPeriod[] no
monday InternetBlockPeriod[] no
tuesday InternetBlockPeriod[] no
wednesday InternetBlockPeriod[] no
thursday InternetBlockPeriod[] no
friday InternetBlockPeriod[] no
saturday InternetBlockPeriod[] no

InternetBlockScheduleExceptions

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/InternetBlockScheduleExceptions
Exceptions to be made for certain devices (MAC addresses). This list have a higher precedence than the Internet Block Schedule set in the device-specific profiles.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
ignoreScheduleAndBlockMACAddresses MACAddress[] no Exceptions to block access for certain MAC addresses.
ignoreScheduleAndAllowMACAddresses MACAddress[] no Exceptions to allow access for certain MAC addresses.

NetworkSecurityProfiles

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/NetworkSecurityProfiles
Profiles that governs the network security feature.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
globalProfile NetworkSecurityRule yes The global profile that is applied for all devices on the network.
deviceSpecificProfiles NetworkSecurityRule[] no The device-specific profiles.

NetworkSecurityRule

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/NetworkSecurityRule
The security rule for blocking or allowing access to the WAN or certain websites from specific devices (MAC addresses).

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
description string no A description of the rule. The maximum length of this value is specified by the maxRuleDescriptionLength member of the GetNetworkSecuritySettingsaction.
This can be used to identify the base rule. Example: "DefaultChild" or "CustomChild"
macAddresses MACAddress[] yes The MAC addresses that are governed by the rule. A given MAC address can only appear once in the list of network security rules. This parameter is required when setting a rule for devices.
Note: deviceSpecificProfiles require this parameter, but globalProfile does not.
internetBlockSchedule InternetBlockSchedule yes The schedule specifying when WAN access should be allowed and blocked during each calendar week.
Note: globalProfile does not support scheduling. However, this parameter is still required for deviceSpecificProfiles
urlWhiteBlackList URLWhiteBlackList no The list of URLs that should be blocked by the rule.
urlBlockedCategoryIDs int[] no The list of categories that is blocked.

PredefinedFilter

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/PredefinedFilter
A pre-defined filter. See wiki for more information.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
filterName string no The name of the pre-defined filter.
urlBlockedCategoryIDs int[] no List of blocked categories in this filter.

SupportedCategory

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/SupportedCategory
This service provides access to a router's subscription-based network security feature. A supported category.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
categoryID int no Unique identifier for the category.
presetName string no A short description of the category.

URLWhiteBlackList

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/URLWhiteBlackList
The URL rule to allow or block certain websites.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
blackList string[] no The list of URLs that should be blocked by the rule.
whiteList string[] no The list of URLs that is allowed by the rule. This feature requires an active subscription.

Enumerations

SubscriptionStatus

http://linksys.com/jnap/networksecurity/SubscriptionStatus
Possible values for the subscription status of the network security feature on the router. We'll add more values as we know more. The goal is to provide more accurate information to clients so they know what to do.

Enumeration Values

Value Description
Active The subscription is active.
Inactive The subscription is inactive.
